There is some evidence that it's related to libs/libstdc++ miscompile, because the following does not crash:

-- if libs are built with llvm-gcc (i.e. no clang-libs stage), everything is fine

-- if clang-newlib is invoked instead of clang-libs, this issue arises: http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2330</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-12-14T00:47:18.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-10-05T19:20:05.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>Clang crashes while building irt</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Defect</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-PNaCl</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns2:label>Mstone-X</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2340/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2340" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/2340" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>2</ns2:stars><ns2:id>2340</ns2:id></ns0:entry>